Underdamped 3D Langevin simulator for multiple trajectories with selectable boundary conditions (free, periodic, reflecting, absorbing).  The script integrates the underdamped Langevin equation using Euler–Maruyama for velocity and a simple position update, supports many trajectories in parallel, and returns time, positions, velocities, and an alive mask for absorbing boundaries. It computes diagnostics: component and radial MSD, the velocity autocorrelation function (VACF), and plots sample 3D trajectories, MSD, VACF, and a final-time radial histogram. Key parameters (mass, friction, temperature, timestep, runtime, number of trajectories, box size, BC type, RNG seed) are exposed at the top of __main__ for quick experiments.
